The paper deals with the analysis of mmWave networks, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The paper also considers the impact of blockages on the network performance, which is a system-level (cs.SY) concern. Additionally, the paper focuses on device-to-device (D2D) networks, which are a specific type of wireless communication system that can be studied in the mobile computing (cs.MM) and performance evaluation (cs.PE) communities.
